  <p class="titletext small">
    For example, while AR may help someone drive by putting directions directly in front of them, it may obstruct their view and delay their reaction time. Some other concerns come from the Ar companies themselves, some believe that AR is not something that their users need or want. For example Google glass was criticized on its aesthetics, and its functionality with claims at its inconvenience and impracticality. Critics claimed that these flaws outweighed its value to the user. Although a large company like Google can withstand a negative reception to a product by users, smaller startup and other companies are worried that a bet on AR is simply not worth it in an economical sense because of the uncertainty about users' responses to new AR products.
</p>
